#: ../../B/benchmark.rst:9
msgid ""
"[techspeak] An inaccurate measure of computer performance. \"In the computer"
" industry, there are three kinds of lies: lies, damn lies, and benchmarks.\""
" Well-known ones include Whetstone, Dhrystone, Rhealstone (see :ref:`h`\\), "
"the Gabriel LISP benchmarks, the SPECmark suite, and LINPACK. See also "
":ref:`machoflops`\\, :ref:`MIPS`\\, :ref:`smoke-and-mirrors`\\."
msgstr ""
"[専門用語]コンピューター性能の不正確な尺度。「コンピューター業界には3種類の嘘がある。嘘、大嘘、そしてベンチマークだ」。よく知られたものに、Whetstone、Dhrystone、Rhealstone(\\"
" :ref:`h`\\ を参照)、Gabriel LISPベンチマーク、SPECmark一式、LINPACKがある。\\ "
":ref:`machoflops`\\ 、\\ :ref:`MIPS`\\ 、\\ :ref:`smoke-and-mirrors`\\ も参照。"
